data.description: RECENTLY UPDATED!! Seller recently made multiple improvements to the home, see list below!Situated in the Francis Marion National Forest on over 2 acres of land with a private deepwater dock on Awendaw Creek and direct access to the community boat ramp, this quaint 2-story farmhouse offers a natural, private setting while still being close to shopping, dining, beaches, and Downtown Charleston. This secluded getaway home has a lovely family room on the 1st floor with a cozy fireplace and a guest half-bathroom. The galley kitchen opens to the dining area, which has access to the screened in- porch. Upstairs, you will find the master with an en-suite bathroom, three additional bedrooms and a second bathroom. Enjoy cool breezes and wooded views from the newly screened in porch or enjoy aglass of wine on your private dock as the sun sets. Outside you will find a large yard leading to the water with a fire pit, a detached two-car garage, workshop and a gardening utility shed. The serene location is unbeatable for lovers of nature and water. Awendaw Creek leads to the Intracoastal Waterway, which leads to the ocean....perfect for boating and fishing. The Francis Marion National Forest offers miles of hiking/riding trails for your enjoyment. This property is approximately 12 miles to McClellanville, 15 miles to Mt Pleasant, 24 miles to Isle of Palms beach, less than 30 miles to downtown Charleston, and 32 miles to Boeing. Here you can be close to it all while surrounded by the beauty of nature. There are so many reasons to love living in the Lowcounty - Incredible weather, stunning natural beauty, thriving marshes and waterways, the ocean, and last but not least, historic Downtown Charleston. New high speed internet is scheduled to be installed in the area by end of 2021- work has already started-per telecom company. Book your showing today!  2021 Updates Include:  New Flooring throughout  Kitchen make-over  New Light fixtures  Screened-in porch makeover  New Front Door  All entry doors, closest and interior walls freshly painted  Bathrooms restored and full make over for 1st floor half bath  Fresh interior paint   Other Improvements include:  2015  New metal roof 2018  New A/C system 2019  New Exterior paint 2020  New fence paint 2020  New water filtration system
